                    <ns0:physDesc>
                        <ns0:objectDesc>
                            <ns0:supportDesc>
                                <ns0:support><ns0:p>Rectangular off-white marble plaque broken down the middle and reconnected. Seemingly intact, but chipped along the left and top edges. The rear is smooth.</ns0:p>
                                    <ns0:material ana="#material.stone.marble" ref="http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/48.html">marble</ns0:material>
                                    <ns0:objectType ana="#object.plaque" ref="http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/259">plaque</ns0:objectType>
                                    <ns0:dimensions>
                                        <ns0:height unit="cm">21.6</ns0:height>
                                        <ns0:width unit="cm">29.5</ns0:width>
                                        <ns0:depth unit="cm">1.7-2.0</ns0:depth>
                                    </ns0:dimensions>
                                </ns0:support>
                                <ns0:condition ana="#condition.complete.broken" />
		    </ns0:supportDesc>
                            <ns0:layoutDesc>
                                <ns0:layout><ns0:p>Five lines of Greek text, centred on the stone, with a consistent left margin, and final line (numerals) centred between ivy leaves.</ns0:p>
                                    <ns0:rs ana="#execution.chiselled" ref="http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1">chiselled</ns0:rs>
                                	<ns0:damage ana="#text_condition.complete" />
			</ns0:layout>
                            </ns0:layoutDesc>
                        </ns0:objectDesc>
                        <ns0:handDesc>
                            <ns0:handNote><ns0:p>Letters are deeply v-cut, somewhat elongated, and showing some tendency towards curvature in e.g. the M. Minial use of serifs. Lunate omega, but rectilinear epsilon and sigma. Alpha with broken bar; mu with four full-length, slanting strokes; kappa with short ams; omicron ovoid but full height; epsilon tall and thin, all bars of equal length; zeta an equal length Z. Use of interpunct to mark off the names, and hedera around the numeral.</ns0:p>
                                <ns0:locus from="line1" to="line1">Line 1</ns0:locus>
                                <ns0:dimensions type="letterHeight">
                                    <ns0:height unit="mm" atLeast="29" atMost="38">29-38</ns0:height>
                                </ns0:dimensions>
                                <ns0:locus from="line2" to="line2">Line 2</ns0:locus>
                                <ns0:dimensions type="letterHeight">
                                    <ns0:height unit="mm" atLeast="25" atMost="30">25-30</ns0:height>
                                </ns0:dimensions>
                                <ns0:locus from="line3" to="line5">Line 3-5</ns0:locus>
                                <ns0:dimensions type="letterHeight">
                                    <ns0:height unit="mm" atLeast="30" atMost="34">30-34</ns0:height>
                                </ns0:dimensions>
                                <ns0:locus from="line1" to="line2">Interlineation line 1 to 2</ns0:locus>
                                <ns0:dimensions type="interlinear">
                                    <ns0:height unit="mm" />
                                </ns0:dimensions>
                            </ns0:handNote>
                        </ns0:handDesc>
